gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nuggets 125, Raptors 119
gameRecap.excerpt: Denver completes a 17-point comeback in the second half to defeat Toronto, 125-119. For Denver, Nikola Jokic led the way recording his 21st triple-double of the season and 126th of his career with 35 points, 17 rebounds, 12 assists, six steals, and two blocks while Jamal Murray added 26 points, 12 assists, and two blocks in the victory. RJ Barrett finished with 26 points, seven rebounds, and nine assists while Kelly Olynyk tallied 24 points and six rebounds for Toronto in the losing effort. Denver improves to 45-20, while Toronto moves to 23-42 in the loss.
